  <h1>Lens</h1>
  <h3>Source</h3>
  <text>
    <style color="0xaaaaaa" italic="true">Note: this page is ported from MCMOD's GTCEu wiki. <br></br>Author: <style color="0xa4e7ff" hover-info="url" underlined="true" url-link="https://center.mcmod.cn/119280/">Oganesson897</style>, <br></br> <style color="0xa4e7ff" hover-info="url" underlined="true" url-link="https://github.com/blackdragon2447">BlackDragon2447</style> <br></br></style>
  </text>
  <text>Lenses are used in the <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:machines/laser_engraver" underlined="true">Laser Engraver</style>, lenses come in two forms, glass lenses and lenses created from gems, since glass lenses require a <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:machines/chemical_bath" underlined="true">HV Chemical Bath</style> you will need to make gem lenses for circuit progression before then. Gem lenses (and <style color="0xbbffaa">Glass lens (white)</style>) are made in the <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:machines/lathe" underlined="true">Lathe</style> using either an <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:materials/exquisite_gem" underlined="true">Exquisite Gem</style> <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:materials/plate" underlined="true">Plate</style> from the right material. From HV on, <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:misc/chemical_dye" underlined="true">Chemical Dye</style> can, and must, be used to create glass lenses of different colors.</text>
